radio_info.short: Welcome to the Twin State and NORPAC Apparatus Profile Project Please select the appropriate template at the right column and download it to your computer.
radio_info.rest:
Fill in the missing information and return email it to the address at the bottom of the template form.

Once received it will be compiled and placed in these folders to the left of this page for review by

mutual aid towns and corrected as needed. Each towns resources will always be available in their folder.

Samples can be found in Littleton Profiles.
In 1982, the Littleton Fire Department was considered to be one of the best-equipped small town fire fighting organizations in the state. Its eight pieces of equipment included (see picture to match apparatus) a 1931 American LaFrance pumper, a 1947 American LaFrance Ladder truck, a 1953 Dodge Maxim pumper, a 1964 American LaFrance pumper, a 1969 Jeep pickup, a 1971 Dodge tanker, a 1972 Chevrolet tanker, and a GMC pumper. The department was staffed by seven full-time men (including the chief) and had a total of twenty-six on call firemen.
